with her parents in Bay Shore.

08:29.676 --> 08:31.887
I've been on my own 11 whole months now.

08:36.850 --> 08:37.851
Wow.

08:39.602 --> 08:40.895
It's beautiful.

08:41.480 --> 08:42.898
It's got the-- Yeah.

08:46.318 --> 08:48.028
"...Daddy of our dreams."

08:49.112 --> 08:50.572
First edition.

08:52.908 --> 08:53.909
It's perfect.

08:55.744 --> 08:58.497
You know, Gretta's dad used to read this
to her when she was little.

08:59.831 --> 09:03.335
Gretta Strickland. That's my wife.

09:05.295 --> 09:06.463
From Alabama,

09:07.798 --> 09:08.924
just like in this.

09:09.883 --> 09:12.344
It's just a story
about a good father, right?

09:13.720 --> 09:16.682
I think her dad used to read this to her
to show her a model of that, you know?

09:17.599 --> 09:19.142
Then she married me.

09:21.311 --> 09:22.688
I wasn't Atticus Finch.

09:22.688 --> 09:25.482
Yeah, well, neither was he.

09:27.234 --> 09:28.402
'Cause of the other book.

09:29.111 --> 09:32.114
I was that man that thought
you just worked and worked,

09:32.114 --> 09:33.991
provided, and that made you a great dad.

09:35.659 --> 09:37.661
But you know what happens
when you do that?

09:38.912 --> 09:44.001
You look up after 25 years,
your wife and your kids,

09:44.001 --> 09:45.294
they don't know you.

09:45.919 --> 09:47.337
All those new dads.

09:47.921 --> 09:50.048
Those guys at the park
with their kids, 6:00 in the morning...

09:55.596 --> 09:56.889
