in my basement, going nuts.

26:29.089 --> 26:32.843
I know this is insane.
At least I'm not alone.

26:39.933 --> 26:41.101
Can I come with you?

26:49.943 --> 26:50.944
Let's roll.

26:51.820 --> 26:52.821
Let's roll.

26:58.911 --> 27:00.495
- Look.
- What?

27:04.458 --> 27:05.459
Hospital beds.

27:06.376 --> 27:07.669
I know where we are.

27:08.754 --> 27:10.881
This must be North Brother Island.
I read about this today.

27:12.591 --> 27:14.551
Yeah,
it was a hospital for the infectious.

27:19.473 --> 27:20.641
Phone died.

27:20.641 --> 27:21.725
Come on, William.

27:22.226 --> 27:23.894
Hey, you know who Mary Mallon was?

27:23.894 --> 27:24.978
Typhoid Mary.

27:24.978 --> 27:26.563
Bingo. You're smart.

27:28.065 --> 27:29.399
The original super-spreader.

27:30.442 --> 27:33.070
You know they quarantined her here
for a third of her life?

27:35.322 --> 27:38.575
Now it's a nesting colony
for the black-crowned night heron.

27:40.202 --> 27:41.203
William!

27:46.250 --> 27:47.960
Hey! Look! Look at that light.

27:48.877 --> 27:52.297
- What is that?
- Holy cannoli. The Wise Ones.

27:52.965 --> 27:55.384
We gotta find out if
these women have weapons and destroy them.

27:55.384 --> 27:58.136
Sabotage their boats.
We could easily take these witches out.

27:58.136 --> 28:01.431
Hey, shut up.
You are a middle-aged IT guy,

28:01.431 --> 28:02.850
and I'm a depressed bookseller.

28:04.560 --> 28:07.354
But I'm the god Apollo.

28:09.773 --> 28:11.567
I am the god Apollo!

28:12.568 --> 28:17.656
Emma! Bitch, where are you? Where are you?

28:19.283 --> 28:25.080
Where are you? Emma! I am the god Apollo!

28:25.581 --> 28:27.749
I am the god Apollo!

28:28.667 --> 28:33.088
I am the god Apollo!
I come for my revenge!

28:33.672 --> 28:39.219
Emma, where are you? Where are you?

28:42.806 --> 28:43.932
Stop!

28:57.779 --> 29:00.032
Let me go. Let me go.

29:01.283 --> 29:03.368
No, no. Let me go.

29:08.415 --> 29:09.791
I'm here for my wife!

29:20.719 --> 29:22.012
Fuck!

29:40.822 --> 29:44.451
<i>When it falls off my wrist,
those three wishes will come true.</i>

29:44.451 --> 29:46.411
<i>I am the god Apollo.</i>

29:46.411 --> 29:50.666
<i>NÃ£o corta</i>. Do not cut it.

29:53.293 --> 29:54.586
It's not a baby.

29:54.586 --> 30:00.425
Hey. No matter what happens,
you're coming with me.

30:01.802 --> 30:07.349
<i>Coming with me. Coming with me.</i>

30:13.480 --> 30:14.565
Stop! Stop!

30:19.236 --> 30:20.487
Get off me!

30:20.487 --> 30:25.158
Why do you protect Emma? Why do you
protect her? She killed my baby!

30:25.158 --> 30:26.827
She killed my baby!

30:27.327 --> 30:28.370
You're Emma's?

30:28.954 --> 30:31.248
Of course he is.
Emma was a pain in the ass.

30:31.248 --> 30:32.541
Why wouldn't the husband be too?

30:32.541 --> 30:34.084
Cal will wanna see you.

30:34.960 --> 30:35.878
- Come on.
- Cal?

30:35.878 --> 30:38.255
Cal told me how to get my daughter back.

30:38.255 --> 30:43.010
Cal told me what to do.
I just don't know if I can do it.

30:43.010 --> 30:44.094
Cal?

30:45.721 --> 30:46.680
Come on.

30:52.769 --> 30:53.770
Get off of me!

30:53.770 --> 30:59.443
Get-- Let me go!

31:00.652 --> 31:01.653
Let me go!

31:13.582 --> 31:14.750
It's not a baby.

31:15.584 --> 31:17.085
Hey, hey, wait!

31:18.420 --> 31:19.421
I know her.

31:34.853 --> 31:36.271
It fell in the courtyard.

31:36.271 --> 31:38.482
One of the children
found it and brought it to me.

31:39.149 --> 31:41.068
I thought I trained you
to be more careful.

31:41.068 --> 31:42.152
I'm sorry.

31:42.736 --> 31:43.737
Sloppy.

31:56.792 --> 31:57.876
Which is more frightening?

32:01.630 --> 32:02.673
Hello?

32:04.299 --> 32:05.968
They didn't cut out your tongue, did they?

32:06.927 --> 32:07.928
You're Cal.

32:09.680 --> 32:12.766
Yeah, it's short for Calisto. Come closer.

32:15.894 --> 32:17.646
They're protective of me.

32:18.647 --> 32:21.233
You're not gonna do anything dumb,
are you?

32:27.906 --> 32:29.575
I'm putting on a show tomorrow
for the kids.

32:29.575 --> 32:32.160
Come, help me make a frightening puppet.

32:32.160 --> 32:35.581
Hey, hey! Where is my wife?

32:35.581 --> 32:40.460
Once upon a time, an old man
and a woman had long wished for a child.

32:40.961 --> 32:42.671
And once pregnant,

32:42.671 --> 32:46.967
the wife gazed longingly at a field
of rapunzel greens next door.

32:46.967 --> 32:50.721
So her husband decided
to steal some for her.

32:50.721 --> 32:54.057
But a terrifying enchantress appeared
and said,

32:54.057 --> 32:58.478
"How dare you, you thief!
I will curse you."

32:59.396 --> 33:02.816
But she agreed
that she would spare his life

33:03.317 --> 33:06.737
if they gave her their baby.

33:06.737 --> 33:08.238
Enough. Stop.

33:09.364 --> 33:12.034
Listen, I need to know where my wife is.

33:12.659 --> 33:14.828
Hey, where is my wife?

33:14.828 --> 33:18.332
I need to find her, all right?
Your whatever tried to kill me.

33:18.332 --> 33:20.250
You know, years ago, a husband found us.

33:21.752 --> 33:26.673
He brought with him two guns and
a ton of rage.

33:27.841 --> 33:29.760
I made the mistake of
trying to talk to him.

33:29.760 --> 33:32.763
But he killed
three women and seven children.

33:34.806 --> 33:36.892
That's when we left the world
and we came here.

33:37.976 --> 33:40.229
And we armed ourselves
as best as we could.

33:40.229 --> 33:45.192
And when men show up,
we're just a little more proactive.

33:52.324 --> 33:53.784
How many men did you kill?

33:55.327 --> 33:56.745
Who knows? We're like the police.

33:56.745 --> 33:58.163
We don't keep track of those numbers.

34:00.290 --> 34:02.251
So, how do we protect our children?

34:03.293 --> 34:06.713
That's what <i>Rapunzel</i> is all about.
That's the question that it's asking.

34:06.713 --> 34:09.174
Well, clearly,
I'm the wrong person to ask.

34:11.592 --> 34:16.223
You know, the husband,
he protects himself over the baby.

34:16.223 --> 34:17.641
The baby gets snatched.

34:18.559 --> 34:19.893
And then the enchantress,

34:19.893 --> 34:21.895
I mean, she won't let that kid go
anywhere in the world.

34:21.895 --> 34:24.313
She's like a helicopter parent.

34:24.313 --> 34:30.404
And still, that prince, he manages
to find a way inside.

34:31.612 --> 34:34.116
I mean, no matter what we do,
the world finds a way in.

34:36.827 --> 34:39.621
So, how do we protect our children?

34:41.706 --> 34:44.877
That's a question that has been asked
for hundreds of years,

34:44.877 --> 34:48.130
ever since fairy tales were first told
around an evening fire.

34:50.340 --> 34:54.303
The new fears are the old fears,
and the old fears are ancient.

34:54.303 --> 34:59.725
But when it's our turn to face them,
they are made new.

35:16.700 --> 35:21.079
The children will talk to this puppet
as if it were as real as me.

35:26.502 --> 35:28.921
It's an old kind of magic.

35:29.796 --> 35:32.591
The Scottish called it "glamour."

35:32.591 --> 35:37.221
It's an illusion where something pretends
to be something other than it is.

35:37.804 --> 35:41.725
A monster looks to be a beautiful maiden,

35:41.725 --> 35:45.312
and a ruined castle appears
as a golden palace.

35:46.396 --> 35:50.150
Do you understand what I'm talking about?

35:53.028 --> 35:54.321
It's not a baby.

35:54.905 --> 35:57.032
That's a smart boy.

36:00.118 --> 36:03.497
But if it's an illusion,

36:03.497 --> 36:05.582
that means there's someone
that created it.

36:05.582 --> 36:09.920
- Hello! Are you in there?
- Shit.

36:11.129 --> 36:12.130
You didn't come alone!

36:38.448 --> 36:39.783
Hey, easy.

36:54.381 --> 36:55.883
What was he doing when you found him?

36:55.883 --> 36:59.344
He was on the shore, waving his
phone light over his head, side to side.

36:59.344 --> 37:01.054
It was dead. The phone was dead.

37:01.054 --> 37:03.140
Why the fuck haven't you destroyed
this thing yet?

37:03.849 --> 37:05.976
I thought you'd like to see
what he has on it.

37:14.151 --> 37:15.235
William.

37:15.235 --> 37:19.489
Oh, my God. This is Gretta's husband.

37:51.772 --> 37:54.525
Yeah, we should call her.
She'll wanna be here when we kill him.

37:54.525 --> 37:57.277
Gretta? Please, I'd love to see her.

37:57.277 --> 37:58.737
That's not gonna happen.

38:13.001 --> 38:14.670
Shit. Okay, okay.

38:21.510 --> 38:26.014
And you, you better decide if you're ready
to eat a large slice of humble pie.

38:40.821 --> 38:44.741
Wait. I don't know what's--

38:55.544 --> 38:56.545
Fuck.

38:57.963 --> 38:59.673
Well, at least I got my glasses back.

39:02.342 --> 39:05.053
How are you not dead, man?

39:14.396 --> 39:15.939
You haven't told me everything.

39:19.401 --> 39:20.736
Well, obviously.

39:23.989 --> 39:27.701
They fucking tried to kill me, man.
They tried to kill me.

39:28.243 --> 39:30.829
Yeah. Yeah, and I'm sorry about that.

39:31.705 --> 39:35.459
But if I'm honest,
I didn't think we'd make it this far.

39:36.084 --> 39:38.921
You know, I've been up and down this river
for months and couldn't find the place.

39:38.921 --> 39:42.841
You went and spotted it on your first try. Lucky.

39:42.841 --> 39:46.345
Wait. If you've been up
and down looking for this place,

39:46.845 --> 39:48.388
you didn't learn
how to drive a boat today.

39:50.265 --> 39:51.642
Well, my family's Norwegian.

39:52.726 --> 39:55.479
Heck, I've been on boats
since I was a baby.

39:56.396 --> 39:57.773
Sailing's just kind of in our blood.

39:57.773 --> 39:59.566
Why would you keep that from me, man?

40:00.817 --> 40:01.902
Doesn't make any sense.

40:08.534 --> 40:10.285
What the fuck is going on, man?

40:11.954 --> 40:12.955
Who are you?

40:13.997 --> 40:18.585
Okay. Okay. I have a confession to make.

40:20.629 --> 40:22.464
I knew who you were before we met.

40:27.427 --> 40:28.846
- What?
- Yeah.

40:30.222 --> 40:32.599
Yeah, I read about your wife
giving birth on the A train.

40:34.434 --> 40:35.811
I just knew.

40:36.436 --> 40:37.354
Just knew what?

40:37.354 --> 40:39.022
That we were gonna be friends.

40:39.982 --> 40:42.985
Oh, my God. This motherfucker is crazy.

40:45.028 --> 40:48.657
This motherfucker is crazy.
Batshit fucking crazy, aren't you?

40:48.657 --> 40:51.827
No, I just loved the story about how Brian
came into the world so much.

40:52.786 --> 40:54.454
You know how you hear about someone
on the news,

40:54.454 --> 40:57.249
so you look them up on the Internet
to see what their life is like now?

40:58.250 --> 40:59.918
Well, I just wanted to see the baby.

41:01.086 --> 41:04.339
And I wanted to find a happy ending
where there was none in my own home.

41:05.549 --> 41:08.051
Let me ask you something. Are you happy?

41:08.051 --> 41:09.845
Are you happy with
my fucking happy ending?

41:09.845 --> 41:12.264
You know, I found you
through all your social media accounts.

41:13.473 --> 41:14.641
Early mornings in the park.

41:15.726 --> 41:17.102
All those pictures you posted.

41:18.228 --> 41:21.481
You were so happy.
And I thought to myself, "I love this guy.

41:22.149 --> 41:25.777
You know, he really gets it. He's doing it
exactly the way I should have done it."

41:25.777 --> 41:29.239
Gretta ran off with my daughter
and destroyed my family, but you--

41:30.199 --> 41:32.367
You were a beacon of what it could be.

41:33.410 --> 41:36.955
Daughter? You have two daughters.

41:38.707 --> 41:39.708
No, I had two.

41:41.460 --> 41:45.380
And then Gretta listened to Cal,
just like Emma did, and she--

41:49.718 --> 41:51.053
I called in the cavalry.

41:51.053 --> 41:54.014
What is that?
What is that, man, the police?

41:55.140 --> 41:56.975
Look, Emma is alive, maybe.

41:57.601 --> 42:00.103
The women on this island
aren't gonna help you find her.

42:01.146 --> 42:02.648
But I can help you.

42:03.690 --> 42:04.775
If you help me.

42:04.775 --> 42:07.986
No, no. Why the fuck would I do that?

42:07.986 --> 42:10.364
After all we've just been through, man,
why the fuck would I do that?

42:10.364 --> 42:12.032
Just help me get Gretta and Grace back.

42:12.032 --> 42:15.536
Well, you heard Cal. They're gonna bring
her here. Help me and I can help you.

42:15.536 --> 42:17.538
Well, you've learned how resourceful I am.

42:17.538 --> 42:19.373
I don't know what the fuck
I've learned about you.

42:20.541 --> 42:23.460
I don't even know who you are
or what the fuck is going on.

42:23.460 --> 42:26.505
I don't know-- I don't know anything, man.
I don't know what the fuck this is.

42:26.505 --> 42:29.758
Please, just talk to Gretta
before they do whatever they're gonna do.

42:29.758 --> 42:31.885
William,
I don't know if you've noticed this,

42:32.386 --> 42:36.723
but I'm in a fucking cage too
with your fucking weird ass!

42:38.308 --> 42:40.394
Well, Cal said she'd kill me and she will,

42:40.978 --> 42:42.604
but she offered you
a chance to eat your pie.

42:43.647 --> 42:45.399
You know,
if you could just talk to Gretta,

42:45.399 --> 42:49.278
explain to her.
I understand it's not her fault.

42:49.862 --> 42:52.239
You know, we both lost our minds
after Agnes died.

42:57.160 --> 42:58.412
That was our baby.

43:00.289 --> 43:02.332
You know, I haven't said her name
out loud in a year.

43:04.376 --> 43:05.377
Agnes.

43:06.795 --> 43:07.796
My sweet girl.

43:09.673 --> 43:11.341
Tell her I know it wasn't her fault.

43:13.177 --> 43:15.929
Tell her I wanna beg for her forgiveness
and offer her mine if she wants it.

43:15.929 --> 43:18.599
- Shut the fuck up. All right.
- I want her and Grace to come home.

43:18.599 --> 43:19.558
All right, all right.

43:19.558 --> 43:21.393
I want what's left of my family
to be whole again.

43:21.393 --> 43:24.271
- I'm just asking you to tell her that.
- All right. Shut up, man.

43:24.980 --> 43:27.274
What makes you think I'm gonna see Gretta
before you do?

43:27.274 --> 43:29.276
Just eat the fucking pie, man!

43:29.902 --> 43:31.403
Just get to my wife.

43:33.780 --> 43:35.199
You're the only chance I have left.

43:37.242 --> 43:38.827
I don't wanna die here without trying.

43:44.541 --> 43:45.792
What if I say no?

43:46.502 --> 43:48.420
If I say, "Fuck you. Fuck all of this"?

43:49.880 --> 43:51.089
Then what?

43:53.425 --> 43:54.635
You don't get it.

43:59.723 --> 44:04.728
Apollo, if you don't help me,

44:04.728 --> 44:07.064
everyone on this island is going to die.
